WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.440
And last week, we had the opportunity to study

00:00:03.440 --> 00:00:05.719
in the Old Testament, we're in the book of Isaiah,

00:00:05.719 --> 00:00:09.720
and we noted how Hezekiah trusted the Lord

00:00:09.720 --> 00:00:12.359
in the midst of great adversity.

00:00:12.359 --> 00:00:13.560
And if you were here last week,

00:00:13.560 --> 00:00:15.399
we looked at that situation,

00:00:15.399 --> 00:00:18.600
and Hezekiah believed the record of creation

00:00:18.600 --> 00:00:20.120
that God had given.

00:00:20.120 --> 00:00:22.879
He knew that God was the creator God,

00:00:22.879 --> 00:00:27.200
and he knew that the creator God was his helper.

00:00:27.200 --> 00:00:29.040
And we mentioned last week,

00:00:29.040 --> 00:00:31.600
as we studied the passage of Scripture there in Isaiah

00:00:31.600 --> 00:00:35.439
with regard to the time of Hezekiah's reign there

00:00:35.439 --> 00:00:38.439
and the attack or the threat of the Assyrians,

00:00:38.439 --> 00:00:41.680
we find that he responded to that great adversity

00:00:41.680 --> 00:00:43.880
with fear, excuse me, with faith,

00:00:43.880 --> 00:00:47.720
and with dependence on God alone to help.

00:00:47.720 --> 00:00:50.479
Faith conquered his fear.

00:00:50.479 --> 00:00:52.919
No doubt, there were opportunities

00:00:52.919 --> 00:00:55.799
for the people of God, Judah,

00:00:55.799 --> 00:00:58.119
to have fear with regard to the threats

00:00:58.119 --> 00:00:59.520
and all that had taken place.

00:00:59.520 --> 00:01:01.360
The Assyrians were the world power

00:01:01.360 --> 00:01:04.000
and had conquered many a people group,

00:01:04.000 --> 00:01:06.000
but Hezekiah was a man of faith.

00:01:06.000 --> 00:01:08.040
Hezekiah was a man that believed God,

00:01:08.040 --> 00:01:11.720
that trusted God, and he knew that God alone

00:01:11.720 --> 00:01:12.599
was able to help.

00:01:12.599 --> 00:01:14.480
He knew that there was nothing that he could do

00:01:14.480 --> 00:01:15.519
and of himself.

00:01:15.519 --> 00:01:19.199
It was all through the power of God the creator

00:01:19.199 --> 00:01:20.519
that was his helper.

00:01:20.519 --> 00:01:22.720
Judah, of course, as we finished up last week,

00:01:22.720 --> 00:01:24.559
was miraculously delivered,

00:01:24.559 --> 00:01:27.080
and the Assyrians were defeated.

00:01:27.080 --> 00:01:29.959
This morning, as we look here in Acts chapter number four,

00:01:29.959 --> 00:01:33.599
I wanna look at what takes place here with the disciples.

00:01:33.599 --> 00:01:36.879
We understand that at this particular time in history,

00:01:36.879 --> 00:01:39.800
as we look at this account in Acts chapter number four,

00:01:39.800 --> 00:01:42.080
that the Lord Jesus Christ had lived

00:01:42.080 --> 00:01:44.959
his perfect, sinless life.

00:01:44.959 --> 00:01:46.959
The record of the life of Christ

00:01:46.959 --> 00:01:49.160
is provided through the gospels.

00:01:49.160 --> 00:01:51.319
We find that he, of course, had gone

00:01:51.319 --> 00:01:53.080
to the cross of Calvary.

00:01:53.080 --> 00:01:54.160
He had bled and died.

00:01:54.559 --> 00:01:55.919
He had been buried in a borrowed tomb,

00:01:55.919 --> 00:01:58.879
and he rose, conquering sin, death, and the grave.

00:01:58.879 --> 00:02:01.080
We find that the book of Acts records for us

00:02:01.080 --> 00:02:03.839
in the first chapter his ascension to heaven,

00:02:03.839 --> 00:02:05.160
and before he ascended to heaven,

00:02:05.160 --> 00:02:07.680
he gave instruction to his disciples,

00:02:07.680 --> 00:02:12.679
to those that would carry on the work of the Lord

00:02:12.679 --> 00:02:17.039
with regard to what we refer to as the Great Commission.

00:02:17.039 --> 00:02:21.160
That work, as the disciples were seeking to fulfill

00:02:21.160 --> 00:02:23.360
the work that God had given them to do,

00:02:23.399 --> 00:02:28.199
was met with serious, I would say intense, opposition.

00:02:28.199 --> 00:02:31.000
We find that many times we begin to read

00:02:31.000 --> 00:02:33.080
through the book of Acts, and as you continue

00:02:33.080 --> 00:02:35.199
through the first several chapters of the book of Acts,

00:02:35.199 --> 00:02:38.800
you read of that opposition to the work of God.

00:02:38.800 --> 00:02:41.360
We've mentioned many times over the years

00:02:41.360 --> 00:02:43.759
that God's work is continuously met

00:02:43.759 --> 00:02:46.800
with opposition, with adversity.

00:02:46.800 --> 00:02:49.800
Just because we're doing what God's called us to do

00:02:49.800 --> 00:02:52.880
doesn't mean that it will be void of any interference

00:02:53.399 --> 00:02:54.559
or any opposition.

00:02:54.559 --> 00:02:58.960
In fact, often we find that that opposition comes greatly

00:02:58.960 --> 00:03:02.000
as we're seeking to follow the Lord.

00:03:02.000 --> 00:03:04.320
The fourth chapter of the book of Acts,

00:03:04.320 --> 00:03:07.039
we're looking this morning, beginning in verse number 23,

00:03:07.039 --> 00:03:10.440
but the beginning of this chapter begins

00:03:10.440 --> 00:03:14.839
by revealing to us how Peter and John were held in prison.

00:03:14.839 --> 00:03:16.559
They were held in prison overnight

00:03:16.559 --> 00:03:19.399
because of what had taken place in Acts chapter number three.

00:03:19.399 --> 00:03:21.639
There was a great miracle that took place

00:03:21.639 --> 00:03:23.440
with that man that was lame,

00:03:23.440 --> 00:03:26.199
that laid at the gate beautiful, and he was healed,

00:03:26.199 --> 00:03:30.199
and that gave opportunity for Peter to preach the gospel,

00:03:30.199 --> 00:03:33.080
and many people trust that Christ is their savior.

00:03:33.080 --> 00:03:36.520
5,000 besides the women, and you look

00:03:36.520 --> 00:03:37.800
at what's taking place there,

00:03:37.800 --> 00:03:41.240
and you look at the growth of the early church,

00:03:41.240 --> 00:03:44.679
and you find that the religious leaders were not happy

00:03:44.679 --> 00:03:47.720
with what was going on, and we find that those

00:03:47.720 --> 00:03:49.320
that believed according to verse number four

00:03:50.119 --> 00:03:52.399
the number of the men was 5,000,

00:03:52.399 --> 00:03:54.479
and as we begin Acts chapter number four,

00:03:54.479 --> 00:03:55.960
they were held in prison overnight,

00:03:55.960 --> 00:03:59.039
they're released, and then they're interrogated,

00:03:59.039 --> 00:04:01.800
and there's all sorts of questions that are asked

00:04:01.800 --> 00:04:05.440
as to what's going on, and we find that Peter stands,

00:04:05.440 --> 00:04:07.679
and he preaches the gospel once again,

00:04:07.679 --> 00:04:10.059
and the religious leaders are not happy

00:04:10.059 --> 00:04:12.320
with what's taking place.

00:04:12.320 --> 00:04:15.360
The religious leaders, they cannot deny the miracle

00:04:15.360 --> 00:04:17.799
of Acts chapter number three, but they desire

00:04:17.799 --> 00:04:20.640
that this would spread no further.

00:04:20.640 --> 00:04:21.480
So what do they do?

00:04:21.480 --> 00:04:24.760
They begin to threaten the disciples.

00:04:24.760 --> 00:04:28.040
We find that the threat is recorded for us.

00:04:28.040 --> 00:04:31.160
Look, if you will, in verse number 17 of Acts four,

00:04:31.160 --> 00:04:34.179
as we make the, set the scene, if you will,

00:04:34.179 --> 00:04:36.679
for the passage that we're going to look at this morning.

00:04:36.679 --> 00:04:39.660
In verse 17, it says, but that it spread no further

00:04:39.660 --> 00:04:44.660
